com.microsoft.office.sfb.appsdk

Interface VideoService

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ConversationService, Observable

    public interface VideoService
extends ConversationService, Observable
    This interface controls the local video that this endpoint sends into the conversation. The results of some operations on this interface may be visible in changes to the ParticipantVideo belonging to the Conversation.getSelfParticipant()

    • Field Detail

      • CAN_SET_PAUSED_PROPERTY_ID

        static final int CAN_SET_PAUSED_PROPERTY_ID
        Property ID for notifying that pause / resume property has changed. Subscribers will be notified via the onPropertyChanged method on the Observable.OnPropertyChangedCallback interface with this property id. E.g. callback.onPropertyChanged(CAN_SET_PAUSED_PROPERTY_ID). Clients are expected to call the isPaused method in the callback to get the changed state.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • CAN_SET_ACTIVE_CAMERA_PROPERTY_ID

        static final int CAN_SET_ACTIVE_CAMERA_PROPERTY_ID
        Property ID for notifying that the a different type of camera (front / back) can be switched to. Subscribers will be notified via the onPropertyChanged method on the Observable.OnPropertyChangedCallback interface with this property id. E.g. callback.onPropertyChanged(CAN_SET_ACTIVE_CAMERA_PROPERTY_ID). Clients are expected to call the canSetActiveCamera method in the callback to get if the camera can be switched.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

        boolean getPaused()

        Returns:
        boolean true is muted false otherwise.
